\id JHN JOHN - Plain English Version 
\h John 
\toc3 John 
\toc2 John 
\toc1 The Good News According to John 
\mt1 John wrote this good news about Jesus  
\mt2 (The book in the Holy Bible called \bk John\bk*)  
\imt1 About this book  
\ip The Holy Bible has 4 books about the things that Jesus did, and the messages he told to people when he was here on the earth, about 2,000 years ago. Those books are in the 2nd part of the Holy Bible, called the \em New Testament\em*. The men that wrote them were Matthew, Mark, Luke, and John. They wrote their books after Jesus went back to heaven. Most of the things in their books happened in the country we now call Israel.  
\ip We have translated everything that John wrote in his book about Jesus. It is important for us today because it tells us about the things Jesus did, and the messages that he brought us from God.  
\ip John was the younger brother of James. Their father’s name was Zebedee. They were fishermen on a lake called Lake Galilee, and it was also called Lake Tiberias. One day, Jesus walked along beside that lake, and he called to James and John, and he told them to follow him (see Mark 1:19-20).  
\ip Later, Jesus picked 12 men to be his special workers, and 2 of them were James and John (see Mark 3:13-19). Those 12 men went everywhere with Jesus for the next 3 years. So John saw and heard most of the things that he wrote about in this book.  
\ip John wrote this book about 50 years after those things happened. That was a long time after Matthew, Mark and Luke wrote their books about Jesus.  
\cl Chapter  
\c 1  
\s1 The one called the Word gave life to everything  
\p
